org.opensha.data

Class ArrayXY_Sequence

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opensha.data.ArrayXY_Sequence
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<XY_Point>, XY_Sequence
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    HazardCurve

    public class ArrayXY_Sequence
extends Object
    Array based implementation of an XY_Sequence.

    This class provides methods for combining and modifying array-based sequences (e.g. add(ArrayXY_Sequence)). These are very efficient implementations that should be used in favor of standard iterators where possible.

    If multiple instances of a sequence with a fixed set of x-values are required, use the copyOf(ArrayXY_Sequence) constructor as it short circuits time-consuming argument validation.

    Author:
    Peter Powers
